      "name": "granny smith apples",
      "amount": "2 medium",
      "notes": "peeled and sliced"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the rolled oats, malted milk powder, and brown sugar.",
    "Add the apple juice and char-grilled yang powder to the bowl and stir until well combined.",
    "Arrange the sliced apples in the bottom of a dolsot-stone-bowl.",
    "Top the apples with the oat mixture and dot with unsalted butter.",
    "Bake the apple bowl in the preheated oven for 25 minutes.",
    "Remove the bowl from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes.",
    "Serve the smoky sweet Dutch apple bowl warm, straight from the stone bowl."
